## Question 13 — Reduction by NaBH₄

### 13.1 — Mechanism and Explanation (5 marks)

Reaction between $\text{NaBH}_4$ and 2-methylbutanal vs 2-methylbut-1-ene.

> **Mark Scheme:**
> * **Mechanism (2 marks):** Arrow from lone pair on $\text{H}^-$ (hydride) attacking the partially positive ($\delta+$) carbonyl carbon. Arrow from the C=O double bond moving to the oxygen atom.
> * **Explanation (3 marks):** $\text{NaBH}_4$ provides a hydride ion ($\text{H}^-$) which acts as a nucleophile. It attacks the electron-deficient / $\delta+$ carbonyl carbon. Alkenes have an electron-rich C=C double bond, which repels the nucleophile.
